node.title: New testing rules introduced in bid to ease pressure on strained healthcare system
node.description: It's hoped testing site queues will be shorter than they were yesterday after national cabinet agreed to remove the requirement for people who test positive to COVID-19 on a rapid antigen test to confirm their case with a PCR test. Follow live.
